MAGIC items in Krynn
====================
Last modified by:
Ckrik, Dec 2021

Weapons:
--------

Draconian Claymore    (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/obj/bclaymore.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      A magical sword that tests the wisdom of its wielder. The
      wielder mentally has to overcome the sword in order to able
      to wield it. (Requirement: WIS > 60)

      The sword is magically balanced, thus behaving lighter in combat
      than it actually is, allowing an increased HIT.

      (Values: hit 49, pen 40).

      It is a two handed weapon.

      Wielded by: Dragon Highlord Kitiara
                  (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/highlord.c)

                  Kitiara appears only in the event of an attack on
                  Vingaard Keep (every 2.6 to 7.6 RL days).

      Wielded by: some Auraks (see below)
                  (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/aurak.c)
                  The highest level auraks may (randomly) have this
                  weapon wielded.

      Wielded by: some Sivaks (see below)
                  (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/sivak.c)
                  The highest level sivaks may (randomly) have this
                  weapon wielded.



Blue Heavy Battleaxe    (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/obj/bbattleaxe.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      A magical axe that tests the strength of its wielder.
      (Requirement: STR > 60)

      The axe is magically made lighter, thus allowing effectiveness
      not normally available in combat. It hits as though it was still
      as heavy as it should be, allowing an increased PEN.

      (Values: hit 32, pen 52).

      It is a two handed weapon.

      Wielded by: some Auraks (see below)
                  (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/aurak.c)
                  The higher level auraks may (randomly) have this
                  weapon wielded.

      Wielded by: some Sivaks (see below)
                  (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/sivak.c)
                  The highest level sivaks may (randomly) have this
                  weapon wielded.


Nightbringer    (/d/Krynn/pax/weapon/nightbringer.c)

   Creator: Jeremiah

   Modified by: Blizzard

   Hit: 45 (50 for player with align < -500)
   Pen: 40

 Special: blind.


 Old: A magical mace, only wieldable by evilaligned players.
      (Requirement: Alignment < -600)

 Now: Wieldable by all players, but those with alignment higher than 0,
      will have it lowered by value of 200. Also, they will get blinded
      for 2-5 minutes, with each attempt to wield. Evil players will have
      the weapon to_hit increased by 5 upon wielding.

      This mace is a 1 handed mace, that draws upon its powers from
      the dark queen Thakisis herself. It has the ability to blind
      its opponent when the right word of command is spoken, 'Midnight'.
      The blinding lasts for about 30 secs. This costs 100 manapoints,
      and the blinding will only be effective if the mace does damage
      in the turn where the word of command is spoken. It is avaliable
      only in combat. If the mace is wielded by Verminaard, it is also
      unbrawlable. Players with alignment higher than 100 will get hurt
      while trying to use the power word.

      It is a 1 handed weapon.

      Wielded by: Dragon Highlord Verminaard
                  (/d/Krynn/pax/monster/verminaard.c)



Wyrmsbane    (/d/Krynn/common/weapons/wyrmsbane.c)

   Creator: Jeremiah

      A magic sword, wieldable by those with alignment > 600.
      It was crafted by the Silvanesti elves during the second dragon
      war, and does extra damage  while fighting dragonkin (ie. Draconians
      and Dragons). The sword is given to the one who kills the slug
      crawling around in the burial chamber of Kith-kanan. The weapon is
      thus only available through combat. The old skeletal remains of the
      elven king, will give the sword to the one who slayed it.

      (Values: hit 35, pen 35). Special dam = dam + dam against dragons
      and draconians, dam * 3 against black dragons.

      It is a 1 handed weapon.

      Wielded by : no one.



Sword of Fire (/d/Krynn/solace/puzzle/weapons/sword_fire.c)

   Creator: Mucalytic

      A magical sword that upon wielding, bursts into flames.
      The fire from the sword produces light, and does fire damage
      to opponents. This object is given as a reward from the
      Solace Puzzle Quest. It is entirely resistant to damage
      by fire, having a resistance of 100. Pen: 32. Hit: 32.
      This sword cannot be bought, and has enchantment magic.

      *** Note the Solace Puzzle Quest is no longer open. 
      *** Nor is this sword.



Bladed Silver Staff     (/d/Krynn/haven/road/bladed_staff.c)

Creator: Morrigan


The bladed silver staff is a magical staff, blessed by the Goddess
of Neutral Magic, Lunitari. It behaves as a "normal" staff, albeit
an exceptional one, when wielded by someone who is _not_ a wizard
of high sorcery. If the wielder is a wizard of high sorcery, and is
on Krynn somewhere, Lunitari will bestow her blessings upon the
follower of the Moons, and the staff will charge itself on one swing,
then the normal swing will be replaced by a magical spell. The spell
will either be a blast of crimson light, or a shower of crimson
light that stuns the opponent for a few seconds.


Wielded by: No one, it is attained from the hooded draconian patrol
near Solace, where it appears randomly. (about 20% of the time)




Elegant Jewel-Encrusted Sabre   (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/obj/kit_sword.c)

Creator: Morrigan

Hit/Pen: 45/40

Magical Abilities: Sentient, Speed

Wielded by:This is the sword of Kitiara the Highlord, who raids VK.


The sword is sentient, very arrogant and ambitious and seeks fame and
fortune. It is jealous, it will not allow itself to be wielded while
the attempted wielder wields another weapon, and the wielder will not
be able to wield another weapon while wielding it. It requires that the
dis of the wielder not be less than 80% of the highest stat, and sword
skill must be >= 60 for the sabre to be wielded. The sword gets angry
in battle, and will begin to glow as its anger increases. When the
fury reaches a certain level it will drain the life of the enemy. The
damage is regular damage for the sabre, but one half of it is directed
at the wielder (all of it is directed at the wielder if it is a killing
blow). The sabre adds a quickness of 33, and sword skill / 10 to parry.
It also will have a random chance to magically parry about 1% of blows
per ten levels of parry (max of 10%). The sabre is particularly jealous
of other magical weapons, and the magical parry chance as well as the
rate in which the sabre gets mad is doubled when fighting an enemy
wielding a magical weapon. Finally, when the sword is angry, there is
a chance that it will force the wielder to attack the largest of his
current enemies.



slender elven longsword (/d/Krynn/icewall/castle2/obj/weapons/fael_sword)

Hit/Pen 47/45

Creator: Kessie

Magical Abilities: Lighter weight, increased hit/pen.

Wielded by: Fael-Thas, General of the White Dragonarmy on Icewall.

This sword has been crafted in Silvanesti for a certain
promising magic user of rich standing. However, found a
user of black arts, and a traitor, he was banned from
Silvanesti, and fled with many a magic item, this sword
included.



sturdy one-bladed axe (/d/Krynn/icewall/castle2/obj/weapons/hrun_axe)

Creator: Kessie

Hit/Pen 34/38 (when wielded by minotaur 40/44)

Wielded by: Hrun, minotaur commander on Icewall.

This is a neat minotaur axe, as per the books. Due to the unique
balance, and heavy axehead, minotaurs and ogres with their huge fists
can do much more damage with it then any other race. The
enchantment upon it is minor.



lethal dragon-forged dagger (/d/Krynn/icewall/castle2/obj/weapons/wknife)

Creator: Kessie and Boron

Hit/Pen 30+random(8)/35+random(10)

Wielded by: Auraks on the whole of Krynn/Ansalon,
            Fael-thas on Icewall.


The weapon supplements the magically forged Claymores and Battleaxes for
the elite troops of Takhisis, Queen of the Abyss.

This nearly a foot long, left handed dagger looks lethal.

Its straight, solid blade has been forged with vicious
teeth set at regular intervals along a razor-sharp
edge that looks capable of cutting skin and bone in
the blink of an eye.A large "color" gem has been mounted
in a steel dragon claw at the end of the hilt, and
serves as the counterbalance.The hilt itself has
been wrapped in the skin of baby dragons.

The weapon glows with a fierce, unholy light, but what
unnerves you the most is the fact that the tiny, not
yet hardened scales on the hilt glow with a silvery
and bronze sheen, and the abominable artifact seems to
emit wails of undescribable agony.



long composite bow (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/singing_bow)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen 44/42 (49/47 as humming long bow, 54/52 as singing elven longbow)

Wielded by: Qualthas in Qualinesti (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/npc/qualthas)

 The bow requires combination of SS_STR and SS_DEX to be wielded.

 It is magicial longbow, that begins to hum in hands of skilled archer,
 and if he is an elf of half-elf the longbows starts changes into 
 singing elven longbow. Its hit and pen changes also (+5 as humming and
 by another 5 as singing bow). If the wielder has at least superior layman
 in SS_WEP_MISSILE, the skill will increase by maximum value of 10 and
 if he is an elf maximum value will be 20. SS_DEFENCE will decrease by
 value equal to gained SS_WEP_MISSILE skill. While being under the 
 influeace of the bow's song, the player's quickness increase by 50.



wide eagle-shaped dagger (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/eagle_dagger)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen 36/35 ( 42/41 if mastered, 28/27 after failed mastering )

Wielded by: Qualthas in Qualinesti (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/npc/qualthas)

 The dagger requires 60 in SS_WEP_KNIFE to be wielded.

 It is a powerfull artifact. The dagger images an eagle stiking its 
 victim and it seems to have its own soul. While wielding player 
 attempts to calm the dagger, what depends on resolve_task (that considers
 TS_INT, TS_WIS, TS_DIS). If it is succesfully mastered the hit and pen
 values increase, if the playes loses those values decrease. Also, during
 the fight the dagger may become wild again and then its stats return to
 normal, unless the command 'gaze into the black onyx eyes' is used. Then
 the wielded will attempt to calm the knife once again. The dagger also
 drains player's mana slowly during the fight.



slender silvery longbow (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/silver_bow)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen: 46/48

Wielded by: Qualthas in Qualinesti (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/npc/qualthas)

 This longbows is wielded by Qualthas as replacement for singing elven bow.
 It was created by Qualinesti elves, who are masters of creating bows, and
 thus it is extremely lethal.


sleek ashwood longbow (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/ash_bow)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen 44/45

Wielded by: Qualinesti elves

 The longbow commonly used by Qualinesti elves, who are masters of creating
 bows. It was made of branch of ash wood by using technic known only to its
 creators. It is extremely light and lethal.


azure rune-etched longsword (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/elven_blade)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen 47/46

Wielded by: noone

 It is Sarist's family longsword. Made of strange azure metal and enchanted
 by elven magic is very light and extremely well balanced, thus lethal. 
 There are runes, that glow during combat, on its blade. The sword can not
 be wielded by evil people. Quest reward.


leaf-headed arrow (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/leaf_arrow)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen 43/43

Used by: Qualinesti elves
 
 Those arrows were made by Qualinesti elves, masters of archery. The arrow
 is perfectly balanced. It has flanged arrowhead to inflic greated damage.  


narrow-headed arrow (/d/Krynn/qualinesti/wep/piercing_arrow)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit/Pen 48/48

Used by: Qualinesti elves


 Those arrows were made by Qualinesti elves, masters of archery. The arrow
 is perfectly balanced and has narrow spiked head, what increases the 
 chance of piercing through armours. 



jet black war-sword (/d/Krynn/pax/weapon/war_sword)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit: 49
Pen: 54

Used by: Verminaard in Pax Tharkas (/d/Krynn/pax/monster/verminaard),

         Kitiara (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/highlord),

Magic abilities: the nasty special, that hits all of the wielder's enemies.


 This composite sword is similar to a great sword but due to its 
 construction it is both lighter and stronger. The sword is made 
 from up to ten strips of metal that are then twisted and forged 
 together  to give a  flexible but strong blade that  can resist 
 more punishment than a standard sword. The blade edges are also 
 combined  with carbon so  that a  sharper edge can be achieved. 
 This is why the sword has increased  damage and a lower weight. 
 It has also the nasty  special, that  allows the wielder to hit 
 all of his  enemies with  a single  swipe, and as a result they 
 may get even stunned (  time : 4 + random(4),  and for  undeads 
 time: 8 + random(4) ). After such attack, the wielder will have
 his parry and defence lowered (by 5) for one minute, however.



dwarven war-mace, "Knee-Crusher" (/d/Krynn/common/weapons/war-mace)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit: 43, (36 if wielded by non-dwarves, 50 if wielded by Neidars)
Pen: 37, (30 if wielded by non-dwarves, 43 if wielded by Neidars)

Used by: Shale the Banished member of the Neidar Clan

                  (/d/Ansalon/balifor/flotsam-forest/living/shale),

         Colin Ironfist, the leader of dwarven merchants
                  (/d/Krynn/haven/dwarf_camp/npc/colin)


 Magic abilities: The mace has damaging special, which if hits the
      enemy's legs will make him unable to walk for a short while. 


 Ths war-mace has was constructed by the Neidar blacksmith long time 
 ago and after that  blessed by priests of Reorx and  thus it is the
 most effective in the hands of a dwarf,  especially hill one. Stats 
 of the war-mace will increase upon wielding by hill dwarves (both 
 +7). His quickness also will be increased by 33. If mace is wielded 
 by non-dwarf, its stats will go down by 7, as it was crafted for 
 dwarven hands. Since the dwarves often fight bigger enemies, like
 ogres, trolls or giants, they usually hit their legs, delivering 
 painfull blows, which may limit the mobility of those creatures. 
 And thus this dwarven war-mace has been named the "Knee-Crusher".

 Every hill dwarf using this mace will become more tired with each 
 hit. Also the offensive style of fighting leaves the hill dwarf
 more vulnerable to attacks (lowering SS_DEFENCE by 5).

 

lethal flame-bladed glaive (/d/Krynn/common/weapons/flame_glaive)

Creator: Blizzard

Hit: 37 (maximum 47)
Pen: 43 (maximum 53)

Used by: Verminaard (/d/Krynn/pax/monster/verminaard),
         the highest level auraks may wield this weapon randomly.       

 Magic abilities: It has a damaging special, which if hits the enemy's
      arms will add attack delay for a short while, but if it hits the
      legs, it will make the enemy unable to move for a moment.

 The weapon consists of a long, broad knife-like bladed attached to a 
 wooden staff. It has a wavy bladed edged on the convex side for 
 slashing and pointed at the tip for trhusting. There are also two
 smaller, crooked blades, which may be used for tearing into opponents
 body. The weapons stats depend on the wielder's SS_WEP_POLEARM skill. 

 The skill of superior layman is required to wield this weapon at all, 
 and only the high races have a chance to use it. In hands of a person 
 whose skill is higher than 55, the stats will increase slightly, but
 if he is a real master of polearm, the stats will increase even more.

 While performing the special attack, the wielder's mana is drained,
 but while being metally exhausted, he will become more tired with 
 every next special hit.



frostreaver (/d/Krynn/icewall/plains/obj/frostreaver)

Creator: Macker/Arman

Hit: 45
Pen: 60

Used by: Icewall Warriors


This battleaxe is made of ice gathered from a secret location on Icewall 
Glacier by the Revered Priests of the Ice Folk. The blade of this weapon 
is formed through a mystical and painstaking process known only to these
priests, however the end result is a weapon as deadly as any! However, 
temperatures above freezing (ie if it leaves Icewall) will eventually rend 
this weapon useless (it melts).



