runed ironwood staff (/d/Krynn/tharkadan/weapon/magic_ironwood_staff.c) 

    Creator : Arman

    This staff was created long before the Catacylsm by a black-robed 
    Wizard of High Sorcery battlemage. Loving the thrill of hand-to-hand 
    combat, he enchanted this staff to draw on the holders magecraft and 
    their skill with the element of wind to empower the staff to be quick 
    in the hands, but powerful enough to fell a warhorse in a hit.

    This weapon gets a bonus to hit/pen depending on the holders SPELLCRAFT 
    and ELEMENT_AIR skills, wielded by /d/Krynn/tharkadan/living/ogre_magi.c 
    The staff is also very light.

    hit = 10 + min(50, who->query_skill(SS_ELEMENT_AIR) / 2);
    pen = 10 + min(50, who->query_skill(SS_SPELLCRAFT) / 2);

    The staff has a clone unique set at 15.    
        
cruel oakwood arrow (/d/Krynn/tharkadan/weapon/poison_arrow.c)

    Creator : Arman

    This arrow has been alchemically enhanced to poison its victims.
    This arrow poisons its target on a hit:
         interval 10
         time 120
         damage:   fatigue 15, hp 50

    Hit 30; pen 30

    These arrows are carried by hobgoblin trackers found along the path
    south of Pax Tharkas with a draconian hunting party:
    /d/Krynn/tharkadan/living/hob_archer.c

    The hunting party only clones when the pass through the mountain is open
    (i.e. not winter).

