      The bozak is a magic user and uses a fire spell as a
      special attack.

      The bones of the bozak explode when he dies.

      Properties: OBJ_I_RES_ACID 80

                  OBJ_I_RES_FIRE 80

                  MAGIC_AM_MAGIC ({ 100, "transmutation"})





Sivak draconian    (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/sivak.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      A magical creature, hatched from eggs of good dragons
      that were enchanted by evil magic.

      The sivak burst into flames when he dies.
      The sivak only appears on the Plains of Solamnia,
      according to a random table, in every room there that
      clones a monster he has a 1/17 chance to appear.

      Properties: OBJ_I_RES_ACID 80

                  OBJ_I_RES_FIRE 100

                  MAGIC_AM_MAGIC ({ 100, "transmutation"})




Aurak draconian    (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/aurak.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      A magical creature, hatched from eggs of good dragons

      that were enchanted by evil magic.

      The aurak does not die the first time he reaches 0 hp,

      instead goes berserk with increased STR, DEX CON and

      DIS, but lower INT and WIS and some new hp. When he

      dies the second time, he turns into a drifting cloud

      and lightning strikes down from it.

      The aurak only appears on the Plains of Solamnia,

      according to a random table, in every room there that

      clones a monster he has a 1/34 chance to appear.

      Properties: OBJ_I_RES_ACID 100

                  OBJ_I_RES_FIRE 100

                  MAGIC_AM_MAGIC ({ 100, "transmutation"})



Skie, blue dragon  (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/skie.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      This is a 'normal' dragon in Krynn. He is quite power-
      ful and has 2 special attacks, a lightning bolt and
      the dragonfear. The lightning bolt can be evaded, but
      has a devastating effect when it hits. The dragonfear
      will add_attack_delay to the enemies.

      All Krynn dragons are magical by nature. They would
      be way too heavy to fly without magical aid anyway.
      Properties: MAGIC_AM_MAGIC      ({ 100, "divination"})

                  OBJ_I_RES_ACID          90

                  OBJ_I_RES_FIRE         100

                  OBJ_I_RES_ELECTRICITY  100

                  OBJ_I_RES_MAGIC         50




Other Objects:

--------------
Enchantable Krynn warfare armours, weapons, and augmentation
   crystals

   Creator: Arman

      See /d/Krynn/common/warfare/rewards/README.txt for
      details.


Teleporting Ring   (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/obj/kitring.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      This is a magical ring that, when worn, will teleport
      the wearer around in Genesis at random intervals.
      There is no way of controlling the ring, not even
      removing the ring will stop the effect. Only dropping
      the ring will stop the teleporting, but if no one else
      picks up the ring, it may just return to the dropper.
      The ring cannot be sold.

      Worn by: Dragon Highlord Kitiara

               (/d/Krynn/solamn/splains/living/highlord.c)

               Kitiara appears only in the event of an attack on
               Vingaard Keep (every 2.6 to 7.6 RL days).



Questmaster's Spectacles (/d/Krynn/solace/village/obj/glasses.c)

   Creator: Aridor

      These are magic spectacles that, when worn, will increase
      the language skill of the wearer by 3-7 skillpoints. The
      glasses are part of the fourth small adventure which involves
      finding the glasses and bringing them to the questmaster.

      The glasses are randomly placed in the area under the Vingaard
      Mountains (/d/Krynn/solamn/thief/*). There is only one pair of
      glasses in the game at any time!

Petrified stick (/d/Krynn/throtyl/obj/petrified_stick.c)

  Creator: Arman

     This is a standard wand that provides some minor spellpower benefits. 
     It is largely used by WoHS to claim the 'stellar alignment' spell 
     from the Tree of Ancestors at /d/Ansalon/guild/neidar/rooms/ancestor_tree.c 

     It also can be used to cast an earth harm spell that has an aid based on 
     the users earth skill and spellcraft (max 75 caid):
     /d/Krynn/throtyl/spells/wand_petrify_spell.c

     It can be obtained by defeating the difficult dwarven ghost doomseeker
     /d/Krynn/throtyl/living/thane_ghost.c

